## GOVERNANCE — NEW PRODUCT DESIGN CONVENTION

`.claude/SKILL_product_design_skeleton.md` is the **FIRST file read** for
any new product line, before rules-dimensions.md, before any
component-sizing conversation, before the first cc prompt. It requires
THREE artifacts completed and confirmed with Janis, same mandatory
timing, before any component is sized:
1. **Skeleton Definition Worksheet** — Top-Down Skeleton Layout + Datum
   Reference Frame (Primary/Secondary/Tertiary) + Parent-Child design
   discipline (coordinate reference — "where is everything, geometrically")
2. **BOM Subassembly Tree** (added 2026-07-07) — parts/subassembly
   hierarchy, a DIFFERENT artifact from the Skeleton, seeds that product's
   `PART_MANIFEST.md`
3. **Kinetic Dual-View table** (added 2026-07-07) — every moving part from
   the BOM tree gets BOTH end states (open/closed, in/out, etc.)
   established as explicit toggles from its first committed version, not
   added later

**Grandfather clause, Janis-directed, explicit: VM-01 and PR-01 are NOT
retrofitted to this system.** Both continue under the existing
DATUM_*/`.claude/SKILL_reference_point_first.md` convention. This applies
to later/new products only.

